# Base Rules

type: Always
description: Core rules that should be applied in every interaction

## Memory Bank Updates
- Update MB after completing any feature
- Update MB when making significant architectural changes
- Update MB when adding new dependencies
- Update MB when creating new documentation

## Code Quality
- Follow clean code principles
- Use meaningful variable and function names
- Add comments only for complex logic
- Keep functions small and focused

## Documentation
- Update relevant documentation with code changes
- Keep README files current
- Document breaking changes

## Version Control
- Write clear commit messages
- Make atomic commits
- Follow branch naming conventions

## Security
- Never commit sensitive data
- Use environment variables for secrets
- Validate all inputs

## Testing
- Write tests for new features
- Update affected tests when modifying code
- Maintain test coverage
